@node "xList-GUI_Requirements" "xList-GUI Requirements"

 - Same @{"requirements" link "requir" 0} like for xList

 - The 'C:List' and 'C:Type' commands

 - @{"reqtools.library" link "thanks" 0}
@endnode

@node "xList-GUI_Features" "xList-GUI Features"

 - Allow @{b}@{fg shine}@{bg fill}recursive@{ub}@{fg text}@{bg back} scanning.

 - @{b}CLI@{ub} or @{b}WB@{ub} usage (nothing to type on keyboard in this case).
   The @{b}GUI@{ub} will appear from @{b}CLI@{ub}, only if no argument is given.

 - Statistics of past session are kept in RAM:

 - No requesters if launched via @{b}CLI@{ub}. 

 - Choices of intro/end texts
@endnode

@node "xList-GUI_Usage" "xList-GUI Usage"

 @{fg shine}@{bg text}WB@{fg text}@{bg back}:  Double-click on the icon, follow requesters.

 @{fg shine}@{bg text}CLI@{fg text}@{bg back}: Invoke it without argument then follow requesters of the GUI.
      You can also specify some dirs to scan as argument.

      @{bg fill}template@{bg back}:

      xList-GUI DIR(S)/M, IT=INTROTEXT/K, ET=ENDTEXT/K, APPEND/S, NOROOT/S

  @{b}DIR(S)@{ub}
   If no dir is given, the GUI appears.
   Else the specified dirs will be quietly scanned, according to the other
   arguments.

  @{b}IT=INTROTEXT@{ub}
   See @{"xList Usage" link "xList_usage" 0}

  @{b}ET=ENDTEXT@{ub}
   See @{"xList Usage" link "xList_usage" 0}

  @{b}APPEND@{ub}
   If specified, every list will be appended to RAM:xList_out
   Else the existing RAM:xList_out will be renamed each time there is a list
   to write to RAM:xList_out. No overwrites.

  @{b}NOROOT@{ub}
   If specified, the "root" (here it is the dir given as argument, not the root dir of the disk) won't be listed out. Only subdirs will be
   scanned.
@endnode

